**Background:** This project wraps pflag and cobra so that very little of these
libraries are visible or usable on the seam.

## Goal

In the past, we used a package `flag/` for managing flags. I'd like to extend
this to now be the entire command line so that we can support new inputs.

I've done _part_ of the refactoring, namely:

* `flag` renamed to `arg`
* `flag.Registrar` renamed to `arg.CommandLine`
* `flag.Unmarshaler` funcs to encompass `*Arg` instead of `*Flag`
* etc

Tests aren't updated to use the new names, docs aren't updated yet.

The goal is to add two new utility functions:

* `arg.Positional[T any](cl *CommandLine, int, &T, ...Option)` to set positional
  arguments. These will come out of the **unparsed arguments** positional by
  index. We'll need to expand `argreg.CommandLine` to support this.
* `arg.Unmatched(cl *CommandLine, *[]string)` to match all unmatched arguments
  that aren't flags or positionals

These funcs will require updates to `argreg.CommandLine` and updates to the
internal `spec` package so that we can process these arguments.

As part of this, update the `help` dialog to now support Positional argument
documentation as well. Like flags, it should appear in a POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
group, with the same color scheme and layout structure as the existing flags.

Update all documentation from the old `flag` package to refer to `arg` instead.

